<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <%- include("../../parts/head") %>
</head>

<body class="d-flex flex-column min-vh-100">

    <!-- Navbar -->
    <%- include("../../parts/navbar") %>

        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="container min-vh-100 bg-light shadow-lg border-start border-end border-dark-subtle">
            <div class="container-content">
                <!-- Hero Image -->
                <div class="row mb-3">
                    <div class="col">
                        <h3>The World of Aeld</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row gap-3">
                    <div class="col-md h-100">
                        <img class="img-fluid h-50 object-fit-cover rounded mb-3" src="/img/aeld.png" />
                        <p class="mt-3">
                            Aeld is an ancient world shaped by the rise and fall of civilizations over eons. Towering
                            mountain ranges divide kingdoms, vast oceans separate distant continents, and untamed
                            wilderness
                            still claims much of the land between. Though monsters, magic, and forgotten ruins exist,
                            they are exceptions rather than the rule. Most people spend their lives farming fertile
                            valleys, working crowded cities, serving noble houses, or traveling the trade roads that
                            connect the world's great powers.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            For adventurers, Aeld is more than a backdrop. It is where reputations are
                            earned, allies are found, equipment is purchased, and fortunes are spent. Between
                            expeditions, its cities offer opportunities to train, conduct research, pursue personal
                            ambitions, forge political connections, and prepare for the next journey into the unknown.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Commonwealth</h6>
                        <p>
                            The Commonwealth encompasses the settled heart of Aeld, where kingdoms, city-states, and
                            free realms stand connected by ancient roads, thriving trade, and centuries of shared
                            history. While every nation governs itself, their borders are bound together by diplomacy,
                            commerce, and necessity. Merchants carry goods across the continent, pilgrims journey
                            between sacred sites, scholars exchange knowledge, and envoys work tirelessly to preserve an
                            often fragile peace.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Yet the Commonwealth is far from peaceful. Political rivalries simmer beneath formal
                            alliances, succession disputes threaten entire kingdoms, and ambitious rulers constantly
                            test the limits of old treaties. Criminal syndicates flourish in crowded cities, forgotten
                            cults gather in hidden places, and ancient relics occasionally surface to upset the balance
                            of power. While armies guard the borders, many dangers arise from within.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Enclave</h6>
                        <p>
                            At the center of the Commonwealth lies the Enclave, the oldest and largest city in the
                            realm. Seat of the Crown and home to the High Council, its towering walls protect
                            generations of history, wealth, and learning. Great temples, universities, guild halls, and
                            noble estates crowd its districts, while merchants from every province fill its markets with
                            goods from across the known world. To most citizens, the Enclave is the embodiment of
                            modern civilization itself.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Heartlands</h6>
                        <p>
                            Surrounding the Enclave, the Heartlands form the productive core of the Commonwealth. Rich
                            farmland, managed forests, quarries, workshops, and foundries provide the food, timber,
                            stone, and manufactured goods that sustain the great city and the provinces beyond. Rivers,
                            canals, and well-maintained roads carry an endless flow of grain, livestock, iron, and
                            finished wares toward the capital, while bustling market towns connect rural communities to
                            the wider realm. 
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Highlands</h6>
                        <p>
                            Rugged mountains and windswept valleys define the Highlands, where hardy communities have
                            carved out lives amid stone, timber, and iron. Rich mineral deposits support mines,
                            foundries, and master smiths whose work is prized across the Commonwealth. Ancient hill
                            forts and weathered castles crown the ridges, remnants of an age when these lands were
                            constantly contested. The people of the Highlands value independence, tradition, and kinship
                            above titles, and while they acknowledge the authority of the Crown, local customs often
                            carry equal weight.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Borderlands</h6>
                        <p>
                            The Borderlands stretch across the outer frontier of the Commonwealth, where civilization
                            steadily gives way to the untamed wilds beyond. Fortified towns, lonely keeps, and weathered
                            watchtowers stand
                            connected by roads that grow fewer and less certain the farther one travels.
                            Soldiers, wardens, trappers, hunters, and adventurers are common sights, for every journey
                            beyond the frontier carries the promise of discovery.
                        </p>
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Highlands</h6>
                        <p>
                            Rugged mountains and windswept valleys define the Highlands, where hardy communities have
                            carved out lives amid stone, timber, and iron. Rich mineral deposits support mines,
                            foundries, and master smiths whose work is prized across the Commonwealth. The people of the Highlands value independence, tradition, and kinship
                            above titles, and while they acknowledge the authority of the Crown, local customs often
                            carry equal weight.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

</body>

</html>